
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Stephanie Haecker — QA Portfolio</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,400;9..144,500;9..144,600;9..144,900&family=Newsreader:ital,opsz@0,6..72;1,6..72&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root{
    --ink:#1c1a17;
    --paper:#f3ede1;
    --paper-2:#ece3d3;
    --rust:#9c4221;
    --rust-bright:#c05621;
    --teal:#1d4d4a;
    --gold:#b7791f;
    --line:#cbbfa8;
    --mut:#6b6354;
  }
  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  body{
    background:var(--paper);
    color:var(--ink);
    font-family:'Newsreader',Georgia,serif;
    font-size:19px;
    line-height:1.65;
    -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;
    overflow-x:hidden;
  }
  .wrap{max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 32px;position:relative;z-index:2}

  /* ---- HERO ---- */
  header.hero{padding:90px 0 60px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);position:relative}
  .eyebrow{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--rust);margin-bottom:28px}
  h1.title{
    font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:900;font-size:clamp(48px,8.5vw,108px);
    line-height:.94;letter-spacing:-.02em;color:var(--ink);max-width:14ch;
  }
  h1.title em{font-style:italic;color:var(--rust);font-weight:500}
  .lede{font-size:clamp(20px,2.4vw,26px);max-width:46ch;margin-top:34px;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.45}
  .lede .name{font-family:'Fraunces';font-weight:600}
  .hero-meta{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px 28px;margin-top:40px;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.05em;color:var(--mut);text-transform:uppercase}
  .hero-meta span{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:9px}
  .hero-meta span::before{content:"";width:7px;height:7px;background:var(--teal);border-radius:50%}

  /* ---- SECTION SCAFFOLD ---- */
  section{padding:74px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  .sec-num{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--rust);letter-spacing:.2em;display:block;margin-bottom:14px}
  h2{font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:600;font-size:clamp(30px,4.6vw,52px);line-height:1.04;letter-spacing:-.015em;max-width:18ch;margin-bottom:30px}
  h2 em{font-style:italic;color:var(--teal)}
  .grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.55fr;gap:46px;align-items:start}
  @media(max-width:760px){.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:22px}}
  p.body{margin-bottom:18px;max-width:62ch}
  p.body strong{font-weight:600}

  /* ---- IMPACT STRIP ---- */
  .impact{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper);border:none;padding:70px 0}
  .impact .wrap{}
  .impact h2{color:var(--paper)}
  .stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px;margin-top:18px;background:rgba(243,237,225,.14)}
  @media(max-width:680px){.stats{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .stat{background:var(--ink);padding:34px 26px}
  .stat .big{font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:900;font-size:54px;line-height:1;color:var(--rust-bright)}
  .stat .lbl{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#cdc4b2;margin-top:14px;line-height:1.5}

  /* ---- FEATURE LIST ---- */
  ul.feats{list-style:none;margin-top:8px}
  ul.feats li{position:relative;padding:18px 0 18px 38px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);max-width:64ch}
  ul.feats li:last-child{border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  ul.feats li::before{content:"→";position:absolute;left:0;top:18px;color:var(--rust);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-weight:500}
  ul.feats li strong{font-weight:600;font-family:'Fraunces';font-size:1.02em}

  /* ---- PILLARS ---- */
  .pillars{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line)}
  @media(max-width:680px){.pillars{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .pillar{background:var(--paper);padding:30px 28px;transition:background .3s}
  .pillar:hover{background:var(--paper-2)}
  .pillar .k{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--rust);margin-bottom:12px}
  .pillar h3{font-family:'Fraunces';font-weight:600;font-size:21px;margin-bottom:10px;line-height:1.15}
  .pillar p{font-size:16.5px;line-height:1.55;color:#403a31;max-width:none}

  /* ---- QUOTE / PRIORITY ---- */
  .frame{border:1px solid var(--line);padding:42px 44px;position:relative;margin-top:10px;background:var(--paper-2)}
  .frame .tag{position:absolute;top:-13px;left:30px;background:var(--rust);color:var(--paper);font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:11.5px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:5px 14px}
  .prio{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0;margin-top:4px}
  .prio-row{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:20px;padding:16px 0;border-bottom:1px dashed var(--line)}
  .prio-row:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .prio-row .n{font-family:'Fraunces';font-weight:900;font-size:40px;color:var(--rust);line-height:1;min-width:54px}
  .prio-row .t strong{font-family:'Fraunces';font-weight:600;display:block;font-size:19px}
  .prio-row .t span{font-size:16px;color:var(--mut)}

  /* ---- SKILLS ---- */
  .tags{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:11px;margin-top:6px}
  .tag{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.03em;border:1px solid var(--ink);padding:9px 16px;border-radius:40px;transition:.25s}
  .tag:hover{background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper)}
  .tag.tool{border-color:var(--teal);color:var(--teal)}
  .tag.tool:hover{background:var(--teal);color:var(--paper)}

  /* ---- CLOSE ---- */
  .close{background:var(--teal);color:var(--paper);border:none;padding:84px 0}
  .close h2{color:var(--paper);max-width:20ch}
  .close .body{color:#dce8e6;max-width:58ch;font-size:21px}

  footer{padding:36px 0;text-align:center;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mut)}

  /* reveal */
  .reveal{opacity:0;transform:translateY(26px);transition:opacity .8s cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.2,1),transform .8s cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.2,1)}
  .reveal.in{opacity:1;transform:none}

  /* ---- FIGURES ---- */
  .figrow{display:grid;gap:22px;margin-top:30px}
  .figrow.two{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
  .figrow.onethird{grid-template-columns:1fr 1.4fr}
  @media(max-width:680px){.figrow.two,.figrow.onethird{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  figure.shot{margin:0;border:1px solid var(--line);background:#fff;padding:10px;box-shadow:0 1px 3px rgba(28,26,23,.06);transition:box-shadow .3s}
  figure.shot:hover{box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(28,26,23,.1)}
  figure.shot img{width:100%;display:block;border:1px solid #eee}
  figure.shot figcaption{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:12px;line-height:1.5;color:var(--mut);padding:11px 6px 4px;letter-spacing:.02em}
  figure.shot figcaption b{color:var(--rust);font-weight:500}
  .redact-note{font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--mut);margin-top:18px;letter-spacing:.04em;opacity:.8}
  figure.shot.dark{background:#0f1b2d;border-color:#1d2d44}
  figure.shot.dark img{border-color:#1d2d44}

</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">QA Engineering · Process · Enablement</div>
    <h1 class="title">Building a QA practice from <em>scratch.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Designing the process, tooling, documentation, and training to support establishing a strong QA team, leading it through to a full platform migration.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="wrap grid">
    <div>
      <span class="sec-num">01 / FOUNDATION</span>
      <h2>A <em>living</em> playbook, not tribal knowledge.</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="body">Established a real testing process where none existed — taking the initiative to move QA from ad hoc to documented and repeatable. Authored the Testing Playbook defining the full sprint workflow — prep, start, and end — and made <strong>"ready for testing"</strong> and <strong>"done"</strong> explicit for everyone.</p>
      <p class="body">Maintained it as a living document: more than a dozen dated revisions from April 2023 through March 2025 — adding security testing, reworking estimation, integrating TestRail test-case repositories, and continually refining the bug workflow. Every revision is versioned and authored, giving the practice an auditable history of how and why it evolved.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="impact">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="sec-num" style="color:var(--rust-bright)">02 / IMPACT</span>
    <h2>What "owned end to end" looks like.</h2>
    <div class="stats">
      <div class="stat"><div class="big">12+</div><div class="lbl">Documented revisions authored across two years</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="big">4</div><div class="lbl">Environments mapped — SIT, QA, UAT, PROD — plus hot-fix paths</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="big">2</div><div class="lbl">Governing documents authored — Playbook then SOP</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="sec-num">03 / SYSTEM</span>
    <h2>A system, not a scramble.</h2>
    <ul class="feats">
      <li><strong>Environment & deployment framework.</strong> SIT → QA → UAT → PROD, including standard and two distinct hot-fix paths with retro-fit logic for code-branch constraints, plus the Gateway-specific UAT-to-Direct-SIT flow.</li>
      <li><strong>Story-point estimation rubric.</strong> Mapped "how much is known to test" and dependency complexity across three non-prod environments — predictable sizing for predictable planning.</li>
      <li><strong>End-to-end bug lifecycle.</strong> Discovery with proof-of-test, blocker linking, routing to the right DEV workspace, retest, and resolution validation — with bug tickets kept in DEV so dev teams retained their sprint points.</li>
      <li><strong>Structured test evidence.</strong> AWS S3 artifacts in a strict project / year / quarter / sprint / ticket hierarchy, with the S3 link posted to each ticket for one-click, interruption-free review.</li>
      <li><strong>Release quality gates.</strong> Geographical peer-review pairs (US:US / PHI:PHI) before every UAT deployment.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="figrow onethird">
      <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>AWS S3 artifact hierarchy</b> — each sprint folder holds per-ticket proof of test. Project / year / quarter / sprint / ticket. (Folder names redacted.)"><figcaption><b>AWS S3 artifact hierarchy</b> — each sprint folder holds per-ticket proof of test. Project / year / quarter / sprint / ticket. (Folder names redacted.)</figcaption></figure>
      <div style="display:grid;gap:22px;align-content:start">
        <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>Copy S3 URI</b> — the link posted back to each ticket for one-click review."><figcaption><b>Copy S3 URI</b> — the link posted back to each ticket for one-click review.</figcaption></figure>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="redact-note">// Usernames, ticket IDs, and project names redacted for public display.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap grid">
    <div>
      <span class="sec-num">04 / STRATEGY</span>
      <h2>Navigating <em>competing</em> priorities.</h2>
      <p class="body">Established how the team decides what protects a release when time is tight — driven by business objectives, project scope, and partner deadlines.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="frame">
        <span class="tag">Priority Framework</span>
        <div class="prio">
          <div class="prio-row"><div class="n">1</div><div class="t"><strong>Project objective achieved</strong><span>Requirements, scope, and ticket detail proven out.</span></div></div>
          <div class="prio-row"><div class="n">2</div><div class="t"><strong>Regression pass</strong><span>Both API and UI suites green.</span></div></div>
          <div class="prio-row"><div class="n">3</div><div class="t"><strong>Supplemental coverage</strong><span>Negative, boundary, and edge-case testing.</span></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="sec-num">05 / ENABLEMENT</span>
    <h2>Promoting best practice &amp; scalability.</h2>
    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillar"><div class="k">Learning Sessions</div><h3>Recorded &amp; reusable</h3><p>Live sessions on project objectives, requirements, and test scenarios — recorded and stored in a shared library so knowledge didn't expire after the meeting.</p></div>
      <div class="pillar"><div class="k">Onboarding Libraries</div><h3>Ramp without hand-holding</h3><p>Video libraries on platform fundamentals — Gateway, tokenization, payment processing — plus role intros for Client Services, BA, and Tech Support, so new engineers and partner teams could self-serve.</p></div>
      <div class="pillar"><div class="k">Reference Material</div><h3>Consistent evidence</h3><p>Distributed examples and templates for test documentation — UI screenshots, API request/response with cURL, and DB/log data validation — keeping proof-of-test uniform across the team.</p></div>
      <div class="pillar"><div class="k">Quality Gates</div><h3>Peer review before UAT</h3><p>Geographical engineer pairs reviewing each other's work prior to UAT deployment — a checkpoint built into the release flow, not bolted on after.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="figrow two" style="margin-top:34px">
      <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="<b>Project testing reference library</b> — recorded platform overviews, regression sessions, estimation process, and configuration walk-throughs."><figcaption><b>Project testing reference library</b> — recorded platform overviews, regression sessions, estimation process, and configuration walk-throughs.</figcaption></figure>
      <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="<b>Onboarding video library</b> — role intros (Client Services, BA, Tech Support) and a Gateway platform overview series for new engineers."><figcaption><b>Onboarding video library</b> — role intros (Client Services, BA, Tech Support) and a Gateway platform overview series for new engineers.</figcaption></figure>
    </div>
    <p class="redact-note">// Owner avatars and a few client-specific file names redacted.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap grid">
    <div>
      <span class="sec-num">06 / CHANGE</span>
      <h2>Leading the <em>migration.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="body">When the organization adopted Monday.com and restructured, it became a chance to improve the operating model — not just swap tools.</p>
      <p class="body">A new Standard Operating Procedure captured the restructured strategy: a flatter <strong>Test Engineer / IT Architect</strong> model, automation candidacy decided in coordination with the architect, and the new geographical peer-review gate before UAT. The previous playbook was formally retired and referenced as the prior version — a clean, documented handoff with no loss of institutional knowledge.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="figrow two" style="margin-top:34px">
      <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>Before — PivotalTracker.</b> Bug workflow: story moved to Rejected, blockers linked to bug tickets, review flagged. (Names &amp; IDs redacted.)"><figcaption><b>Before — PivotalTracker.</b> Bug workflow: story moved to Rejected, blockers linked to bug tickets, review flagged. (Names &amp; IDs redacted.)</figcaption></figure>
      <figure class="shot dark "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>After — Monday.com.</b> Per-environment subitems (SIT / QA / UAT / PRD) plus an automation-candidate row, each with status &amp; priority."><figcaption><b>After — Monday.com.</b> Per-environment subitems (SIT / QA / UAT / PRD) plus an automation-candidate row, each with status &amp; priority.</figcaption></figure>
    </div>
    <div class="figrow two">
      <figure class="shot "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>PivotalTracker ticket state</b> — review status kept current so the team could see progress without interrupting the tester."><figcaption><b>PivotalTracker ticket state</b> — review status kept current so the team could see progress without interrupting the tester.</figcaption></figure>
      <figure class="shot dark "><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="<b>Monday.com QA bug task</b> — typed as QA Bug, owner assigned, full proof-of-test and description captured. (Title &amp; detail redacted.)"><figcaption><b>Monday.com QA bug task</b> — typed as QA Bug, owner assigned, full proof-of-test and description captured. (Title &amp; detail redacted.)</figcaption></figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="sec-num">07 / TOOLKIT</span>
    <h2>Skills &amp; tools.</h2>
    <div class="tags">
      <span class="tag">QA Process Design</span>
      <span class="tag">Test Strategy &amp; Prioritization</span>
      <span class="tag">Story-Point Estimation</span>
      <span class="tag">Bug Lifecycle Management</span>
      <span class="tag">Release Quality Gates</span>
      <span class="tag">Documentation &amp; Governance</span>
      <span class="tag">Team Enablement &amp; Training</span>
      <span class="tag">Process Migration</span>
    </div>
    <div class="tags" style="margin-top:16px">
      <span class="tag tool">PivotalTracker</span>
      <span class="tag tool">Monday.com</span>
      <span class="tag tool">TestRail</span>
      <span class="tag tool">GitHub</span>
      <span class="tag tool">AWS S3</span>
      <span class="tag tool">cURL / API Testing</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="close">
  <div class="wrap">
    <span class="sec-num" style="color:#9fd0cb">08 / THE THROUGHLINE</span>
    <h2>Make testing depend on a process — not a person.</h2>
    <p class="body">Documented, versioned, traceable, and teachable. That's the standard behind this work, and the standard brought to a team. Happy to walk through any of these artifacts in detail.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<footer>
  <div class="wrap">Stephanie Haecker · Professional Portfolio</div>
</footer>

<script>
  const obs=new IntersectionObserver((es)=>{es.forEach(e=>{if(e.isIntersecting)e.target.classList.add('in')})},{threshold:.12});
  document.querySelectorAll('section .wrap, .hero .wrap').forEach((el,i)=>{el.classList.add('reveal');el.style.transitionDelay=(i%2*.08)+'s';obs.observe(el)});
</script>

